theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A)))))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  -- Collapse the innermost pattern using the 4-level idempotence lemma.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))))) =
        closure (interior A) := by
    simpa using
      (Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
        (X := X) (A := A))
  -- Rewrite the larger expression using `h₁`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A)))))))) =
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
    simp [h₁]
  -- Collapse once more with the 2-level idempotence lemma.
  have h₃ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
    simpa using
      (Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
        (X := X) (A := A))
  simpa [h₃] using h₂

theorem Topology.interior_interior_closure_eq_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (interior (closure A)) = interior (closure A) := by
  simpa [interior_interior]
